cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and machine translation. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a method for detecting machine-translated text using AI techniques. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the proposed method involves training a model to identify coherence in paragraphs. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper deals with identifying and filtering out unnatural machine-translated text, which is important in information retrieval tasks. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the impact of machine translation on communication between different communities.
